        <h1>LeetCode 3689: Maximum Total Subarray Value I (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an integer array nums and an integer k. You can perform operations on subarrays of nums.
                In each operation, you can select a subarray and add the difference between its maximum and minimum
                element multiplied by k to the total value. Find the maximum total value you can achieve.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,2,3,4,5], k = 2<br>
                Output: 8<br>
                Explanation: The maximum element is 5 and the minimum element is 1. The difference is 5 - 1 = 4.
                Multiplying by k gives 4 * 2 = 8.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    long long maxTotalValue(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums, int k) {
        long long largest = 0, smallest = INT_MAX;
        for (int idx = 0; idx &lt; nums.size(); idx++) {
            if (nums[idx] &gt; largest) largest = nums[idx];
            if (nums[idx] &lt; smallest) smallest = nums[idx];
        }
        // Find overall minimum and maximum element
        return (largest - smallest) * k;
    }
};</code></pre>
